<li id="cite_note-151"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-151">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/blog/2012/mar/02/stasi-museum-berlin-erch-mielke">"The Guardian" 2 March 2012</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-152"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-152">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Koehler (1999), pages 54-55.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-153"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-153">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/book-review-philip-kerrs-field-gray/2011/04/18/AFP6RjdE_story.html">Book Review: Philip Kerr's 'Field Gray'</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Washington_Post" title="The Washington Post">The Washington Post</a></i>, 24 April 2011.</span>
</li>
